{"lemma": "طَسْتٌ", "slug": "طَسْتٌ", "root": "ط.س.ت", "root_slug": "ط-س-ت", "root_link": "/words/roots/ط-س-ت", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n26714"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "basin", "fa": "سینی", "ur": "طشت", "tr": "tes", "id": "baskom", "bn": "টাস্ট", "es": "palangana", "fr": "bassin", "de": "Becken", "ru": "таз", "zh": "盆"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n26714", "headword_ar": "طَسْتٌ", "root": "Tst", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K, &c.)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A kind of vessel of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Sufor", "text_ar": "صُفْر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "brass"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (M, TA:) [generally pronounced in the present day"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ti$ot", "text_ar": "طِشْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ta$ot", "text_ar": "طَشْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and mostly applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a kind of basin of tinned copper,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of brass,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of silver, used for washing the hands &c.,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "figured and described in my work on the Modern Egyptians:]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tas~N", "text_ar": "طَسٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [q. v.,] (IKt, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) which is [said to be] arabicized from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tasot", "text_ar": "طَسْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the latter being a foreign word; (Mgh;) [but it is from the Pers.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ta$ot", "text_ar": "طَشْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";] it is of the dial. of Teiyi; (S;) and [said to be] formed from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tas~N", "text_ar": "طَسٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", one of the two"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (IKt, S, Msb, K,) because they are deemed difficult of pronunciation; (IKt, S, Msb;) but in forming the pl. and the dim., the second"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is restored, because separated from the former; (S;) for (IKt, S, Msb) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TisaAsN", "text_ar": "طِسَاسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TusuwsN", "text_ar": "طُسُوسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", though it has also for its pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TusuwtN", "text_ar": "طُسُوتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (IKt, Mgh, Msb,) or, accord. to Zj,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TisaAtN", "text_ar": "طِسَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;) and the dim. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TusayosN", "text_ar": "طُسَيْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TusayosapN", "text_ar": "طُسَيْسَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (IKt, Msb:) it is also pronounced"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TisotN", "text_ar": "طِسْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (MF;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ta$otN", "text_ar": "طَشْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also has been mentioned; (K;) but some say that this is a mistake; and others, that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ta$ot", "text_ar": "طَشْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the original word from which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TasotN", "text_ar": "طَسْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is arabicized: (TA:) Zj says that, with most of the Arabs, (Msb,) it is fem.: (Mgh, Msb:) sometimes it is masc.: (Lh, M:) IAmb says, on the authority of Fr, that the word used by the Arabs was"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tas~apN", "text_ar": "طَسَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", save that some said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tas~N", "text_ar": "طَسٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and that the tribe of Teiyi said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TasotN", "text_ar": "طَسْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as they said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "liSotN", "text_ar": "لِصْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "liS~N", "text_ar": "لِصٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": Es-Sijistánee says that it is a foreign word arabicized: and Az, that it is a word adopted into the Arabic language, because"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "T", "text_ar": "ط"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "t", "text_ar": "ت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "do not both occur in an Arabic word. (Msb.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "TA", "IKt", "S", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "Lh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}